%N A395442 Squares visited by six knights, all starting on square 1, when moving on a square-spiral numbered board and always moving to the lowest available unvisited square.
%C A395442 All six knights, numbered 1..6, start at square one, and each moves in turn to the lowest available unvisited square, starting with the lowest numbered knight.
%C A395442 The sequence is finite - knight 3 is trapped on square 819 after visiting 195 squares, knight 6 is trapped on square 1378 after visiting 276 squares, knight 2 is trapped on square 1160 after visiting 286 squares, knight 4 is trapped on square 3431 after visiting 1229 squares, knight 5 is trapped on square 11379 after visiting 4059 squares, and knight 1 is trapped on square 11697 after visiting 6765 squares, giving a total of 12805 visited squares.
%H A395442 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A395442/b395442.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..12805</a>
%H A395442 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A395442/a395442.png">Image of the knights' paths</a>. The knights' paths are colored red, yellow, green, blue, indigo and violet, the final squares for knights 2..6 are colored yellow, and the final square for knight 1 is colored red.
